======================================================================
ANALYSIS 8: VITALI HIERARCHY — NON-MEASURABILITY GROWTH WITH n
======================================================================

The "non-measurable" fraction of tournament structure grows with n:

At each n, let:
  - N_score = number of distinct score sequences
  - N_H = number of distinct H values
  - N_total = number of distinct tournaments (up to isomorphism)

The "measurability ratio" = N_score / N_total tells us what fraction
of structure is score-determined. As n grows, this ratio -> 0.

n=3: 2 score classes, 2 H values, 0 score classes with multiple H values (0.0%)
  Max H values in a single score class: 1
n=4: 4 score classes, 3 H values, 0 score classes with multiple H values (0.0%)
  Max H values in a single score class: 1
n=5: 9 score classes, 7 H values, 1 score classes with multiple H values (11.1%)
  Max H values in a single score class: 3
n=6: 22 score classes, 19 H values, 9 score classes with multiple H values (40.9%)
  Max H values in a single score class: 6
n=7: 59 score classes, 77 H values, 38 score classes with multiple H values (64.4%)
  Max H values in a single score class: 16

